ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project

Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: R = Right; L = Left; B = Both; 999= No Answer; 888= Skipped; 777= Condition Skipped; 555= Missing

ElementDescription: Trial Duration and Units ie 20 minutes
Inter trial interval (ITI) duration and units
Description of SCR value calculated at the per-trial level
Mean SCR value across all trials of type 1
Mean SCR value across first 5 trials of type 1
Mean SCR value across last 5 trials of type 1
Mean SCR value across all trials of type 2
Mean SCR value across first 5 trials of type 2
Mean SCR value across last 5 trials of type 2
Mean SCR value across all trials of type 3
Mean SCR value across first 5 trials of type 3
Mean SCR value across last 5 trials of type 3
Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
Neutral Stimuli: SCE (spec. and non) Event Count
Positive Stimuli: SCE (spec. and non) Event Count
Negative Stimuli: SCE (spec. and non) Event Count

ValueRange: American Indian/Alaska Native; Asian; Hawaiian or Pacific Islander; Black or African American; White; More than one race; Unknown or not reported; Other Non-White; Other

ElementDescription: Structured Clinical Interview for DSM-5 (SCID) diagnosis for ANXIOUS GROUP ONLY
Notes: Examples are Social Anxiety Disorder, Depression, PTSD, Other Anxiety Disorder, etc

ElementDescription: Subject rating of how much social support is provided by selected figure on a daily basis
Notes: 1 = No social support; 10 = A lot of social support

ElementDescription: Counterbalanced version of stimulus presentations viewed by subject

Notes: 1 = Training stage; 2 = Acquisition stage; 3 = Extinction stage; 4 = Extinction test stage; 5 = Fear reinstatement test

ElementDescription: RAW SCR data from fear reinstatement test
